  "description": "Add a new speaking-focused practice module 'Tag Question Drill' that helps users master English tag questions (e.g. 'You're coming, aren't you?'). Tag questions are a frequent stumbling block for learners because they require (a) correct auxiliary/pronoun agreement and (b) the right intonation (falling = seeking confirmation, rising = genuine question).\n\nBackend (new file `app/routers/tag_questions.py` registered in `app/main.py`):\n- GET `/api/tag-questions/session?difficulty=beginner|intermediate|advanced&count=8` тАФ returns a session of statements needing tags. Generate via Copilot with a structured prompt (add `build_tag_question_prompt` to `app/prompts.py`) returning JSON: `{ items: [ { statement, expected_tag, expected_intonation: 'rising'|'falling', context_hint, explanation } ] }`. Include a small static fallback list (8 items) if Copilot fails, following the pattern used in `app/routers/linker_drill.py` / `phrasal_verbs.py`.\n- POST `/api/tag-questions/attempt` тАФ body `{ statement, expected_tag, expected_intonation, user_tag, user_intonation }`. Grades: tag-text match (normalized lower/strip punctuation) and intonation match. Returns `{ tag_correct, intonation_correct, score (0тАУ100), feedback }`. Persist via existing `record_practice_event` / metrics pattern so it shows in dashboard totals.\n\nNo schema changes required (reuses existing practice_events-style logging). If a new events table is introduced, include the corresponding `ALTER TABLE`/`CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` in `_MIGRATIONS`. Prefer logging through the existing generic practice metric path тАФ no migration needed.\n\nFrontend (`frontend/src/pages/TagQuestionDrill.tsx` + route entry in `frontend/src/App.tsx` and a card on the Home page):\n- Session UI shows the statement, a text input for the tag (with optional chips for common auxiliaries: isn't/aren't/don't/doesn't/didn't/won't/can't/shouldn't), and two buttons for intonation: тЖШ Falling (confirm) / тЖЧ Rising (ask). Submit triggers grading; feedback panel shows correct tag, intonation reason, and a 'Listen' button that uses the existing TTS helper (see `linker_drill` / `monologue` frontends) to play the full sentence with the target intonation cue (append тЖШ/тЖЧ to the text-to-speech prompt or use two different pitch SSML hints if available; otherwise just two TTS calls).\n- Results screen: tag accuracy %, intonation accuracy %, list of missed items with explanations, Retry and Back-to-Home buttons. Match dark-mode styling used across other drill pages.\n\nTests:\n- `tests/unit/test_tag_questions_router.py`: mock Copilot to return a canned session; test grading endpoint for correct tag + intonation, wrong tag, wrong intonation, and normalization (trailing '?', case).\n- Extend `tests/integration/test_app.py` (or add a new integration file) to cover the happy path GET+POST flow.\n\nThis adds a fresh speaking/listening feature not overlapping with any of iterations 673тАУ693 (no existing tag-question, auxiliary, or intonation-of-question drill).",
