  "description": "Add a new grammar drill that targets a notoriously hard contrast for Japanese learners: past simple vs. present perfect (and present perfect continuous). Users see a short scenario sentence with a blank (e.g., 'I ___ (live) in Tokyo since 2019.') and must type the correctly conjugated verb form. After each item, the UI shows the correct answer, a 1-line 'why' explanation (time marker cue, state vs. completed event, etc.), and marks right/wrong. A session is 8 items; results show score, per-tense accuracy (past simple vs present perfect vs present perfect continuous), and weak cues. Wrong items are auto-retried at session end.\n\nBackend (app/routers/tense_contrast.py):\n- POST /api/tense-contrast/session -> returns 8 items. Each item: {id, sentence_with_blank, verb_lemma, correct_form (list of acceptable forms e.g., ['have lived','have been living']), tense_label ('past_simple'|'present_perfect'|'present_perfect_continuous'), cue (e.g., 'since 2019'), explanation}. Items are generated via copilot_client with a deterministic system prompt in app/prompts.py (add TENSE_CONTRAST_SYSTEM). Validate via Pydantic; fall back to a small static bank of ~20 items in app/routers/tense_contrast.py if LLM fails (tests use the fallback).\n- POST /api/tense-contrast/submit -> body: {session_id, answers: [{item_id, user_answer, correct, tense_label, elapsed_ms}]}. Persists to new table tense_contrast_attempts.\n- GET /api/tense-contrast/stats -> per-tense accuracy over last 30 days (for dashboard card later).\n\nDAL (app/dal/tense_contrast.py): create_attempts(attempts), get_stats(days=30).\n\nDatabase (app/database.py SCHEMA): add table tense_contrast_attempts(id INTEGER PK AUTOINCREMENT, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, session_id TEXT NOT NULL, item_id TEXT NOT NULL, tense_label TEXT NOT NULL, user_answer TEXT, correct INTEGER NOT NULL, elapsed_ms INTEGER).\n\nMigration to add to _MIGRATIONS in app/database.py (CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS is fine here because it is a brand-new table, but add anyway for consistency):\n  \"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS tense_contrast_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, session_id TEXT NOT NULL, item_id TEXT NOT NULL, tense_label TEXT NOT NULL, user_answer TEXT, correct INTEGER NOT NULL, elapsed_ms INTEGER)\"\n\nRouter wiring: register tense_contrast router in app/main.py alongside other routers.\n\nFrontend (frontend/src/pages/TenseContrast.tsx + route entry): Page with Start button -> fetches session -> renders one item at a time with a text input, Submit button, instant feedback (green/red + explanation + correct forms), progress bar (x/8). Results screen shows total score, per-tense accuracy bars, list of missed items with correct answer + explanation, and a 'Retry missed' button that re-runs just the wrong items. Add a card entry on the Home page linking to /tense-contrast. Support Enter-to-submit and keyboard focus management. Include dark-mode styles consistent with other drill pages (see Paraphrase/Linker).\n\nTests: tests/unit/test_tense_contrast_dal.py covering create_attempts + get_stats with mixed tenses and date filter; plus an API test that POSTs /submit with the static fallback session and asserts stats update.",
